Gravestone Doji

    Definition: A bearish reversal pattern with open and close near the low, a long upper shadow, and no lower shadow.
    Criteria:
        Body: abs(close - open) ≤ 5% of range.
        Upper shadow: high - max(open, close) ≥ 70% of range.
        Lower shadow: min(open, close) - low ≤ 5% of range.
    What It Tells a Trader:
        Bearish Reversal: Buyers pushed prices up, but sellers closed near the low, indicating strong selling pressure.
        Context-Dependent: Effective at resistance after an uptrend.
    How to Trade It:
        Entry: Short at the close or on bearish confirmation (e.g., breakdown below the Doji’s low).
        Stop-Loss: Above the Doji’s high (1-2x atr14).
        Take-Profit: Next support (2-3x risk).
        Confirmation: RSI 50-70, ADX < 25, high volume_surge_ratio, order_book_imbalance < 0.5.
        Futures Notes: Low leverage, stops above high, monitor bid_ask_spread.